---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { withBase } from "../config.mjs";

const updated = "June 22, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  path="/privacy-policy/"
  description="The official privacy policy for KaiZenly+. The app is local-first: no developer server, no account, no tracking or analytics. Your data stays on your device in an encrypted database and is never sent to the developer."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-top:10px">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-top:16px">
        This is the official privacy policy for KaiZenly+. In short: the developer does not collect
        your data, the app has no tracking, and everything you create stays on your device. For a
        friendlier walk-through, see the <a href={withBase("/privacy/")}>Privacy overview</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:40px">
        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Who this policy is from</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ (“the app”) is made by one solo student developer based in Pakistan. There is no
          company, no marketing network, and no data team behind it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">What data the developer collects</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>None.</strong> KaiZenly+ has no developer server or backend. Your habits, journals,
          moods, schedules, and settings are never sent to the developer. The app has no analytics
          SDK, no advertising identifiers, and no background reporting. Normal use does not need an
          internet connection at all.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Where your data lives</h2>
        <p>
          Everything you create stays <strong>on your device</strong> in an <strong>encrypted</strong>
          database. App preferences are stored locally on the device too. Nothing is uploaded unless
          you personally choose to make a backup.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Encryption</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is <strong>encrypted</strong>. The app’s on-device data is encrypted, your local
          backups are encrypted, and the optional Google Drive backup file is already encrypted
          before it leaves your phone. A backup is unlocked only by a password <strong>only you
          know</strong> — it is never stored and never sent anywhere.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Optional Google Drive backup</h2>
        <p>
          Google Drive backup is <strong>optional, manual, and opt-in</strong>. If you enable it, you
          sign in with <strong>your own</strong> Google account and the app uploads one
          already-encrypted file to a private app folder in your Drive that only KaiZenly+ can see.
          Backups go to your Drive — <strong>never</strong> to the developer. Your use of Google
          Drive is also covered by Google’s own privacy policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Permissions</h2>
        <p>
          Some features (mainly Focus / Zen Shield) need device permissions. They are requested only
          when you enter a feature that needs them, and each one is explained on the
          <a href={withBase("/permissions/")}>Permissions page</a>. The Accessibility service used
          during a focus session reads only app package and class names for enforcement — it does
          <strong>not</strong> read your messages, passwords, keystrokes, or screen content.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Children’s privacy</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ does not collect any personal data from anyone, including children. It is a
          general self-improvement tool and is not directed at children under 13.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Keeping or deleting your data</h2>
        <p>
          Because your data lives only on your device, <strong>you</strong> control it completely.
          Deleting a backup or uninstalling the app removes the data from that location. There is no
          developer copy to request or delete, because the developer never had it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Third parties</h2>
        <p>
          The only third party involved is Google — and only if you choose to use Google Drive
          backup, through your own account. No data is sold or shared with advertisers, brokers, or
          anyone else.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If server, backend, AI, or MCP features are ever added, this policy will be updated before
          any data behaviour changes. Those features are only a possible future direction today.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          A public contact email will be added here before the Google Play launch. Until then, see
          the <a href={withBase("/about/")}>About</a> page to learn more about the developer.
        </p>

        <p class="muted" style="margin-top:32px;font-size:0.88rem">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:32px">
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={withBase("/data-safety/")}>Data Safety</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={withBase("/terms/")}>Terms &amp; Conditions →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
